In this article, President Donald Trump issues proclamations to celebrate the signing of the Constitution and to recognize its role in securing liberty for the country. He emphasizes the importance of self-government and the need for the government to act with accountability and consent from the governed. Trump also calls for regulations to be authorized by duly enacted statutes and for ineffective and burdensome regulations to be eliminated. He encourages federal agencies to make room for states, local communities, religious and civic organizations, and individual Americans to address problems with innovative solutions. The article concludes with Trump proclaiming September 17 as Constitution Day and Citizenship Day, and September 17-23 as Constitution Week. He celebrates the citizens and the Constitution that have made America a great nation and reiterates the commitment to the enduring principles of the Constitution.